    "comment": "Rationale: The authors use an antibody specific for PLC B4 in immunoelectron microscopy studies. PLC B4 was detected at the postsynaptic ER in both pre-embedding EM(Figure 5). In line with a localization to the ER, in subcellular fractionation, PLC-B4 was detected in a fraction that is also enriched in IP3R (Figure 6).\n\nThe antibody against PLC B4 is verified by western blot against PLC B4 knockout (Figure 1).. Experimental description: Adult C57BL mice at 2-3 months of age were used in the present\nstudy, with the exception of ICR mice for immunoprecipitation.",
